This paper deals with the complexity and rewritability of ontology-mediated queries, which are commonly studied in the fields of databases and artificial intelligence. Therefore, cs.DB and cs.AI are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also heavily relies on the description logic EL, which falls under the category of logic and reasoning (cs.LO). Additionally, the paper involves analyzing the structure of queries, which can be related to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and computational complexity (cs.CC).
